Whenever you are creating new files, looking for files to modify, or generally need to understand "what goes where" in this project, reference this rough outline below:

/.cursor/agents/ -> Cursor **subagents** (markdown + YAML frontmatter); isolated context. See Cursor docs: Subagents.
/__tests__/ -> all of our Vitest + react testing library stuff - unit tests for all our code
/docs/ -> all of our documentation, from PRDs to technical docs.
/src/ -> all the source code
    /app/
        /api/ -> all API routes apart from Supabase auth routes go here
            /sessions/ -> session CRUD, join, actions, extract
            /inventory/ -> player inventory and loadout management
            /trader/ -> buy/sell cards
            /profile/ -> player profile read/update
            /quests/ -> quest listing with progress
        pages that import features and common components. Dont implement features here.
    /components/ -> **common** components across all pages and features
    /features/ -> actual feature implementations. Implement the actual features here.
    /lib/ -> backend services and business logic
        /types.ts -> shared TS types, Zod schemas, enums
        /supabase/ -> Supabase clients + SQL schema files (tables.sql, security.sql, functions.sql, seed.sql)
        /game/ -> game.service, game.repo, rules (validation), scoring, rng
        /session/ -> session.service, session.repo (lifecycle management)
        /inventory/ -> inventory.service, inventory.repo (player cards and loadout)
        /economy/ -> economy.service, economy.repo (M$, XP, trader, profile)
        /quests/ -> quest.service, quest.repo
        /effects/ -> effect registry + handler plugins
        /realtime/ -> Supabase Realtime broadcast helpers
    global-config.json -> global config values such as feature flags and global params
.env -> environment variables in the format 'NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=your-project-url' (no quotes)
       Required vars: NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL, NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY, SUPABASE_SECRET_KEY (service role / secret key; legacy name SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY may still appear in older docs)